declarations.name: Input

attributes.name: autocomplete-inline
attributes.description:
When true, the component inserts the best suggestion into the input field
as inline text. The appended portion of the suggestion is selected so the
user can accept it (e.g. press Enter) or continue typing to replace it.
Typically combined with `autosuggestInline` to display candidates while
typing.

attributes.name: autocomplete-list
attributes.description:
When set and not `'custom'`, `applyAutocompleteList()` filters the
listbox options to items that start * with the typed text. This controls
dropdown filtering but does not itself cause inline insertion.

attributes.name: autosuggest-inline
attributes.description:
When true, the component advances/searches suggestion candidates as the
user types (calls `changeSuggestion({ startsWith })`). If
`autosuggestInline` is true and `autocompleteInline` is also true the
current candidate will be shown inline; if `autocompleteInline` is false
only the candidate selection changes (no inline text insertion).

attributes.description: If true, when listbox is open, arrow navigation will automatically select options.

attributes.name: accept-on-escape
attributes.description: If true, when listbox is open, <Esc> accepts current suggestion (same as Enter).

members.name: ariaAutocompleteAttrValue
members.description:
Compute `aria-autocomplete` to describe the widget's behavior to AT.

ARIA values:
- `none`  : no autocomplete behavior is provided
- `inline`: the textbox shows an inline completion the user can accept
- `list`  : a popup listbox provides choices (no inline insertion)
- `both`  : both inline completion and a listbox are available

Component mapping:
- `autocompleteInline` -> inline completion behavior
- `autocompleteList` (non-null) -> listbox filtering / dropdown present
- `autosuggestInline` -> drives candidate selection as user types

Note: the current implementation reports `'both'` when a named
`autocompleteList` is present (even if `autocompleteInline` is false).
A stricter mapping would return `list` when only a listbox is present
and `both` only when both `autocompleteInline` and a listbox exist.

attributes.description: Leading slot content or shorthand string.

attributes.name: avatar
attributes.description: Avatar label or shorthand content for a leading avatar.

attributes.name: avatar-color
attributes.description: Color token used for the avatar container (default: primary-container).

attributes.name: avatar-src
attributes.description: Image source for the avatar.

attributes.name: src

attributes.description: Alt text for the leading image.

attributes.name: icon-ink
attributes.description: Ink/color token used for the leading icon.

attributes.description: External image/SVG source for the leading icon.

attributes.name: icon-variation
attributes.description: Icon variation (e.g., 'filled').

attributes.name: checkbox
attributes.description: Checkbox shorthand name or placement class for a selectable leading checkbox.

attributes.name: radio
attributes.description: Radio shorthand name or placement class for a selectable leading radio.

attributes.name: selection-color
attributes.description: Selection color token used when item is selected (default: primary).

attributes.description: Trailing text slot or shorthand.

attributes.description: Divider style identifier (e.g., 'inset').

attributes.description: If true, indicates the list item contains video content and adjusts layout.

attributes.description: Number of text lines the item should reserve for content (integer).

declarations.name: ListOption

attributes.name: selected
attributes.description:
Initial/default selection state (reflected to `selected` attribute).
Use `selected` property to control runtime selection.

attributes.name: label
attributes.description:
Explicit label for accessibility. Reflected to attribute `label`.
Falls back to `textContent` when not provided.

attributes.name: text
attributes.description: Explicit text content for the option. Reflected to attribute `text`.

attributes.name: value
attributes.description:
Underlying option value (reflected to `value` attribute). Defaults to
the option's text content when not provided.

attributes.name: state-layer
attributes.description: Show the visual state layer element when true

members.name: delegatesFocus
members.description: When true, the element delegates focus to an internal focus target.

Text content for the option; setting updates the internal `_text` field.

members.description:

members.description:

the option's text when not explicitly defined.

declarations.description:
List options represent selectable choices within a `mdw-listbox` or list.
@see https://m3.material.io/components/lists/specs

declarations.name: Listbox

attributes.name: multiple
attributes.description: When true, multiple options may be selected (select-multiple semantics).

attributes.name: size
attributes.description: Visible size (number of rows) for the listbox; 0 means auto.

members.name: delegatesFocus
members.description: When true, the element delegates focus to an internal focus target.

members.name: kbdNav
members.description: Enable keyboard roving navigation when present (set to 'true').

members.name: kbdNavQuery
members.description:
Query used to find roving tab index children
Query selector used by keyboard navigation mixin to find focusable options.

members.name: kbdNavFocusableWhenDisabled
members.description:
Flag whether disabled elements participating in roving tab index
should be focusable.
Allow keyboard navigation to focus disabled options in some patterns.

members.name: kbdNavChildren
members.description: List of roving tab index participating children

members.name: disabled
members.description: Whether the element is disabled (affects interactive states)

members.name: focused
members.description: Force focus state (independent of document)

members.name: hovered
members.description: Force hover state (independent of interaction)

members.name: pressed
members.description: Force pressed state (independent of interaction)

members.name: stateLayer
members.description: Show the visual state layer element when true

members.name: ariaControls
members.description: ARIA 'controls' attribute (string).

members.name: autocomplete
members.description: Autocomplete token for the associated control (string).

members.name: name
members.description: Name attribute for the control used in forms.

members.name: readOnly
members.description: Read-only state reflected to control via 'readonly' attribute.

members.name: formNoValidate
members.description: When true, form validation is skipped for this control (formnovalidate).

members.name: defaultChecked
members.description: Default checked state for checkable controls (checkbox/radio).

members.name: required
members.description: Whether the control is required for form submission.

members.name: type
members.description:
Control type token (e.g. 'text','checkbox','radio','file').
Returns the control type string compatible with `input`/`select` semantics.

members.name: checked
members.description:
Part of FormAssociatedMixin for simplicity.
Enumerability doesn't guarantee checked state will be passed or used.

members.name: multiple
members.description: When true, multiple options may be selected (select-multiple semantics).

members.name: size
members.description: Visible size (number of rows) for the listbox; 0 means auto.

members.name: density
members.description: Density level affecting spacing and compactness. Integer from -4 (dense) to 4 (spacious).

members.name: color
members.description:
Palette or surface token used to select background/ink tokens.
Examples: 'primary', 'background', 'surface-container-low'.
Visual color token for list surfaces. Default is `surface` to match
Material surface theming.

type.text: <K extends StringKeyOfARIAMixin<keyof ARIAMixin>>(name: K, value: ARIAMixin[K]) => void

members.name: block
members.description: Set `display: block` on the host (boolean)

members.name: inline
members.description: Use inline flex layout: `display: inline-flex` (boolean)

members.name: row
members.description: Switch main axis to horizontal: `flex-direction: row` (boolean)

members.name: x
members.description:
Main-axis alignment / justification.
Allowed: 'start'|'center'|'end'|'between'|'around'|'stretch'|'baseline'.
Default: 'start'.

members.name: y
members.description:
Cross-axis alignment / alignment of items.
Same allowed values as `x`. Default: 'start'.

members.name: gap
members.description: Gap between children. Accepts preset numeric strings (e.g. '8') mapped to px, or floats.

members.name: padding
members.description: Padding preset or numeric value (e.g. 'pane', '8', '16').

members.name: ink
members.description:
Explicit ink override token (e.g. 'outline', 'on-primary', 'inverse-on-surface', 'inherit').
Maps to `--mdw-ink`.

members.name: typeStyle
members.description:
Typographic style shortcut that maps to type scale variables
(e.g. 'headline-large', 'body-medium').

members.name: delegatesFocus

Flag whether disabled elements participating in roving tab index
should be focusable.

members.name: kbdNavChildren
members.description: List of roving tab index participating children

members.description: Density level affecting spacing and compactness. Integer from -4 (dense) to 4 (spacious).

members.name: modal

members.name: native

members.name: scrollable
members.description: Allow internal content to scroll when true

members.name: matchSourceWidth
members.description: When true, match the popup width to the source element

members.name: flow
members.description: Placement strategy for the popup ('corner').

members.name: popupMargin
members.description: Margin between popup and viewport/anchor (px)

members.name: useHistory
members.description: Whether to push/pop history entries when opening the popup

members.name: returnValue
members.description: Optional return value for dialog-like popups

members.name: color

members.description:
Typographic style shortcut that maps to type scale variables

members.name: shapeBottom

members.name: shapeStart

members.name: shapeEnd

declarations.name: MenuItem

attributes.name: value
attributes.description:
Backing field for the menu item's value attribute. Can be `null` to
indicate no explicit value; reflected to the `value` attribute.

attributes.name: cascades
attributes.description: ID of the submenu to open when this item cascades.

attributes.name: state-layer
attributes.description: Show the visual state layer element when true

members.name: ariaControls
members.description: ARIA 'controls' attribute (string).

members.name: autocomplete
members.description: Autocomplete token for the associated control (string).

members.name: name
members.description: Name attribute for the control used in forms.

members.name: readOnly
members.description: Read-only state reflected to control via 'readonly' attribute.

members.name: formNoValidate
members.description: When true, form validation is skipped for this control (formnovalidate).

members.name: defaultChecked
members.description: Default checked state for checkable controls (checkbox/radio).

members.name: required
members.description: Whether the control is required for form submission.

members.name: type
members.description: Control type token (e.g. 'text','checkbox','radio','file').

members.name: defaultValue
members.description:
Non-null string representation of the default value used for form
association. Getter never returns null; setter writes to `_defaultValue`.

members.name: value
members.description:
Option `value` used when the option is selected in a form. Defaults to
the option's text when not explicitly defined.

members.name: checked
members.description:
Part of FormAssociatedMixin for simplicity.
Enumerability doesn't guarantee checked state will be passed or used.

members.name: CASCADE_TIMEOUT
members.description: Milliseconds to delay before opening a cascaded submenu.

members.name: cascades
members.description: ID of the submenu to open when this item cascades.

members.name: delegatesFocus
members.description: When true, the element delegates focus to an internal focus target.

members.name: href
members.description: The URL that the hyperlink points to.

members.name: target
members.description: The browsing context in which to open the linked resource (e.g. '_blank').

members.name: download
members.description: Suggested filename for download.

members.name: ping
members.description: URLs to be pinged when the link is followed.

members.name: rel
members.description: Link relationship tokens (e.g. 'noopener', 'noreferrer').

members.name: hreflang
members.description: Language of the linked resource.

members.name: referrerPolicy
members.description: Referrer policy for the link (serialized to 'referrerpolicy' attribute).

members.name: kbdNavFocusableWhenDisabled
members.description:
Flag whether disabled elements participating in roving tab index
should be focusable.

members.name: kbdNavChildren
members.description: List of roving tab index participating children

members.name: scrollable
members.description: When true the tablist is scrollable (renders differently).

members.name: tabContentId
members.description: Id of an external `TabContent` element to bind and observe.

members.name: active
members.description: Whether the tablist is visually active (has a selected tab).

members.name: secondary
members.description: Render the secondary (label-width) indicator style when true.

members.name: selectedIndex
members.description:
Modifiable index of the currently selected tab. 0-based index.
Setting this updates tab `active` states accordingly.

members.name: selectedItem
members.description:
Modifiable currently selected tab.
Setting this updates tab `active` states accordingly.

members.name: updateIndicator
members.description: Recompute and apply indicator; optionally disable animation when `animate` is false.

members.name: updateIndicatorByPosition
members.description:
Update the indicator position by a floating `percentage` between 0..1
representing the scroll progress across tab panels.

members.name: observeTabContent
members.description: Observe the bound TabContent scroll and update indicator accordingly.

type.text: (current?: HTMLElement, loop?: boolean, reverse?: boolean) => HTMLElement

declarations.name: TabPanel

attributes.name: active
attributes.description: Whether this panel is active/visible; updates ARIA `aria-hidden`.

attributes.name: peeking
attributes.description: True when the panel is partially visible (peeking).

members.name: active
members.description: Whether this panel is active/visible; updates ARIA `aria-hidden`.

members.name: peeking
members.description: True when the panel is partially visible (peeking).

type.text: <K extends StringKeyOfARIAMixin<keyof ARIAMixin>>(name: K, value: ARIAMixin[K]) => void

members.name: block
members.description: Set `display: block` on the host (boolean)

members.name: inline
members.description: Use inline flex layout: `display: inline-flex` (boolean)

members.name: row
members.description: Switch main axis to horizontal: `flex-direction: row` (boolean)

members.name: x
members.description:
Main-axis alignment / justification.
Allowed: 'start'|'center'|'end'|'between'|'around'|'stretch'|'baseline'.
Default: 'start'.

members.name: y
members.description:
Cross-axis alignment / alignment of items.
Same allowed values as `x`. Default: 'start'.

members.name: gap
members.description: Gap between children. Accepts preset numeric strings (e.g. '8') mapped to px, or floats.

members.name: padding
members.description: Padding preset or numeric value (e.g. 'pane', '8', '16').

members.name: color
members.description:
Palette or surface token used to select background/ink tokens.
Examples: 'primary', 'background', 'surface-container-low'.

members.name: ink
members.description:
Explicit ink override token (e.g. 'outline', 'on-primary', 'inverse-on-surface', 'inherit').
Maps to `--mdw-ink`.

members.name: typeStyle
members.description:
Typographic style shortcut that maps to type scale variables
(e.g. 'headline-large', 'body-medium').

declarations.name: Table

members.name: caption
members.description:
The table caption element (`mdw-caption`) or `null` when not present.
Mirrors `HTMLTableElement.caption` semantics.

members.name: tHead
members.description:
The table header section (`mdw-thead`) element or `null` when not present.
Mirrors `HTMLTableElement.tHead` semantics.

members.name: tFoot
members.description: The table footer section (`mdw-tfoot`) element or `null` when not present.

members.name: tBodies
members.description:
Live `HTMLCollection` of `mdw-tbody` elements contained by the table.
Mirrors `HTMLTableElement.tBodies`.

members.name: rows
members.description:
Live `HTMLCollection` of row elements (`mdw-tr`) in the table.
Mirrors `HTMLTableElement.rows`.

members.name: createCaption
members.description: Create and return a `mdw-caption` element, appending when necessary.

members.name: deleteCaption
members.description: Remove the table's caption element when present.

members.name: createTHead
members.description: Create and return a `mdw-thead` element for the table.

members.name: deleteTHead
members.description: Remove the table's `mdw-thead` element when present.

members.name: createTFoot
members.description: Create and return a `mdw-tfoot` element for the table.

members.name: deleteTFoot
members.description: Remove the table's `mdw-tfoot` element when present.

members.name: createTBody
members.description: Insert and return a new `mdw-tbody` element before the tFoot (if any).

declarations.name: TextArea

attributes.name: value
attributes.description: Forwards a `value` attribute to the internal `defaultValue`.

attributes.name: fixed
attributes.description: When true the textarea is fixed-size and will not auto-resize.

attributes.name: minrows
attributes.description: Minimum number of rows to display. Mirrors the `minrows` attribute.

attributes.name: maxrows
attributes.description: Maximum number of rows to allow when auto-resizing.

attributes.name: dirname
attributes.description: The `dirname` attribute value forwarded to the native control.

attributes.name: maxlength
attributes.description: Maximum allowed characters for the control.

attributes.name: minlength
attributes.description: Minimum required characters for the control.

attributes.name: rows
attributes.description: Number of rows to render; updated when resizing.

attributes.name: wrap
attributes.description: Wrapping behavior token forwarded to the native control.

attributes.name: state-layer
attributes.description: Show the visual state layer element when true

members.name: delegatesFocus
members.description: When true, the element delegates focus to an internal focus target.

members.name: disabled
members.description: Whether the element is disabled (affects interactive states)

members.name: focused
members.description: Force focus state (independent of document)

members.name: hovered
members.description: Force hover state (independent of interaction)

members.name: pressed
members.description: Force pressed state (independent of interaction)

members.name: stateLayer
members.description:
Show the visual state layer element when true
Show an internal visual state layer element

members.name: color
members.description:
Palette or surface token used to select background/ink tokens.
Examples: 'primary', 'background', 'surface-container-low'.

members.name: ink
members.description:
Explicit ink override token (e.g. 'outline', 'on-primary', 'inverse-on-surface', 'inherit').
Maps to `--mdw-ink`.

members.name: typeStyle
members.description:
Typographic style shortcut that maps to type scale variables
(e.g. 'headline-large', 'body-medium').

members.name: shapeTop
members.description: Show top cut/shape on the element

members.name: shapeBottom
members.description: Show bottom cut/shape on the element

members.name: shapeStart
members.description: Show start-side cut/shape (logical start)

members.name: shapeEnd
members.description: Show end-side cut/shape (logical end)

members.name: shapeStyle
members.description: Predefined shape size/style name (none|extra-small|small|medium|large|extra-large|full|inherit)

members.name: outlined
members.description:
When true, an outline is rendered around the element
When true, use outlined styling

members.name: density
members.description: Density level affecting spacing and compactness. Integer from -4 (dense) to 4 (spacious).

members.name: ariaControls
members.description: ARIA 'controls' attribute (string).

members.name: autocomplete
members.description: Autocomplete token for the associated control (string).

members.name: name
members.description: Name attribute for the control used in forms.

members.name: readOnly
members.description: Read-only state reflected to control via 'readonly' attribute.

members.name: formNoValidate
members.description: When true, form validation is skipped for this control (formnovalidate).

members.name: defaultChecked
members.description: Default checked state for checkable controls (checkbox/radio).

members.name: required
members.description: Whether the control is required for form submission.

members.name: type
members.description:
Control type token (e.g. 'text','checkbox','radio','file').
Input type (text, password, email, etc.)
The control type used by the component.

members.name: defaultValue
members.description: The default value (initial value) of the internal textarea.

members.name: checked
members.description:
Part of FormAssociatedMixin for simplicity.
Enumerability doesn't guarantee checked state will be passed or used.

members.name: controlTagName
members.description: Tag name used for the native control element.

members.name: controlVoidElement
members.description: Textareas are not void elements.

members.name: icon
members.description: Leading icon key/name to render inside the field

members.name: iconVariation
members.description: Variation of the icon display (e.g., filled)

members.name: label
members.description: Floating label text for the field

members.name: filled
members.description: When true, use filled styling

members.name: inputPrefix
members.description: Prefix text shown before the input

members.name: inputSuffix
members.description: Suffix text shown after the input

members.name: trailingIcon
members.description: Trailing icon key/name

members.name: trailingIconInk
members.description: Ink/color token for the trailing icon

members.name: trailingIconLabel
